The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Sunday, September 07, 2003 				 Health pledge
 A STAFF REPORTER																								State health minister Surjya Kanta Mishra announced that the government would shortly take up the task of upgrading facilities at all the medical colleges and hospitals. He was inaugurating the states first installed blood component separating machine at RG Kar Medical College and Hospital on Saturday.																								The machine will help doctors ensure the purity of blood components and is also a step towards modernisation of blood banks in the city and the districts.
